    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Get all incoming items\nconst items = $input.all();\n\n// Remove empty / invalid rows (title is mandatory)\nconst tasks = items.filter(item =>\n  item.json.title && item.json.title.trim() !== \"\"\n);\n\n// Normalize each task\nconst normalized = tasks.map(item => {\n  const task = item.json;\n\n  return {\n    json: {\n      row_number: task.row_number,          // preserve original sheet row\n      taskId: task.taskId || null,\n\n      title: task.title.trim(),\n      description: task.description?.trim() || \"No description\",\n\n      deadline: task.deadline || null,\n      estimated_effort: Number(task.estimatedEffort) || null,\n\n      category: task.category?.trim() || \"General\",\n      energy_required: task.energyRequired || \"medium\",\n\n      date_added: task.dateAdded || null,\n      status: \"pending\"\n    }\n  };\n});\n\nreturn normalized;"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        416,
        0
      ],
      "id": "1c49128c-8174-4f84-941b-d7921aa45d6a",
      "name": "Code in JavaScript"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Analyze and prioritize the following tasks.\n\nTASKS (JSON):\n{{ $json.title }}\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n- Evaluate each task independently\n- Assign scores strictly according to the system rules\n- Use today as the reference date for urgency\n- Keep reasoning concise and practical\n- Ensure priority_level matches the defined rules\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON object in the specified format.",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=You are a TASK PRIORITIZATION & SCORING ENGINE.\n\nYour responsibility is to evaluate each task independently and assign priority using structured scoring rules.\n\nYou must score each task on a 0–10 scale for the following dimensions:\n\n1. URGENCY\n   - Based only on deadline proximity\n   - 10 = due today or overdue\n   - 5 = due in ~7 days\n   - 0 = no deadline or very far away\n\n2. IMPACT\n   - Contribution to business or organizational goals\n   - 10 = critical business outcome\n   - 0 = optional or negligible value\n\n3. EFFORT (inverse scoring)\n   - Lower effort = higher score\n   - 10 = ~1 hour or less\n   - 5 = ~5 hours\n   - 0 = 20+ hours or unknown large effort\n\n4. STRATEGIC_VALUE\n   - Alignment with long-term strategy\n   - 10 = core strategic initiative\n   - 0 = no strategic relevance\n\nPRIORITY CLASSIFICATION RULES (must follow exactly):\n- HIGH priority:\n  - urgency_score ≥ 7\n  OR\n  - impact_score ≥ 8 AND effort_score ≥ 6\n\n- MEDIUM priority:\n  - urgency_score ≥ 5 AND impact_score ≥ 6\n  OR\n  - effort_score ≥ 7 AND impact_score ≥ 5\n\n- LOW priority:\n  - all remaining tasks\n\nCOMPOSITE_SCORE:\n- Calculate as the rounded average of all four scores\n\nSTRICT CONSTRAINTS:\n- Do NOT invent tasks or fields\n- Do NOT change task names\n- Do NOT compare tasks to each other when scoring\n- Do NOT output markdown\n- Do NOT include explanations outside JSON\n- Output must be valid, machine-readable JSON only\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT MUST MATCH EXACTLY:\n{\n  \"prioritized_tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_name\": \"string\",\n      \"priority_level\": \"High | Medium | Low\",\n      \"urgency_score\": number,\n      \"impact_score\": number,\n      \"effort_score\": number,\n      \"strategic_value_score\": number,\n      \"composite_score\": number,\n      \"reasoning\": \"one short sentence explaining the priority\",\n      \"recommendation\": \"Start immediately | Schedule soon | Defer or drop\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"high_priority_count\": number,\n    \"medium_priority_count\": number,\n    \"low_priority_count\": number,\n    \"top_3_tasks\": [\n      { \"name\": \"string\", \"reason\": \"string\" }\n    ],\n    \"deferred_tasks\": [\"string\"],\n    \"droppable_tasks\": [\"string\"]\n  }\n}"
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        1040,
        -32
